<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<FrameLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:id="@+id/fragment_container_eggplant"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent">
<androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="#DAF7A6">
    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent">
    <RelativeLayout
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:padding="16dp"
        tools:context=".HydroponicPlantActivity">

        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView"
            android:layout_width="200dp"
            android:layout_height="200dp"
            android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
            android:src="@drawable/eggplant" />

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/nutrientsTextView"
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_below="@id/imageView"
            android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="16dp"
            android:fontFamily="sans-serif-medium"
            android:text="Nutrients from Plant:

Eggplants, like many fruiting vegetables, require essential macronutrients (nitrogen, phosphorus, potassium) and micronutrients (calcium, magnesium, iron, etc.) for healthy growth. In hydroponics, a balanced nutrient solution is crucial to support eggplant's leaf, flower, and fruit development."
            android:textColor="#070707"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/growingDurationTextView"
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_below="@id/nutrientsTextView"
            android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="16dp"
            android:text="Plant Growing Duration:

The growth duration for hydroponic eggplants can vary depending on the specific eggplant variety, environmental conditions, and the hydroponic system used. On average, it takes around 70 to 85 days from seed to harvest for most hydroponically grown eggplant varieties"
            android:textColor="#070707"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/diseaseTextView"
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_below="@id/growingDurationTextView"
            android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="16dp"
            android:text="Diseases Occurring During Growth:
Eggplants can be susceptible to various diseases, including:

Verticillium and Fusarium wilt: These soil-borne diseases are less likely to occur in hydroponic systems because they are soilless.

Powdery mildew and aphids: These can affect eggplants, especially in conditions of high humidity. Proper humidity control and regular monitoring are essential in hydroponics to prevent these issues."
            android:textColor="#070707"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

        <Button
            android:id="@+id/eggplant_button"
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_below="@id/diseaseTextView"
            android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="16dp"
            android:background="@drawable/button_background"
            android:text="Buy Nutrition"
            android:textColor="#ffff"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

    </RelativeLayout>

    </ScrollView>

</androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout>
</FrameLayout>